To run the CIREPI coal flame: 
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

Step-1. Run the simulation with one-step flame sheet chemistry without injecting
 fuel particles. 
    -- Turn on the flame sheet particle chemitry. 
        Modifying /CASE/constant/cloudProperties:
        reactionModel    flameSheetParticleChemistry;

Step-2. When the "fast" flame is nicely developed (a complete flow through is 
recommended), switch to finite rate chemistry with pilot only. 
    -- Pause the simulation. 
        Modifying /CASE/system/controlDict:
        stopAt    endTime;
    -- Reconstruct the latest time step and delete all the processors. 
        calling ./ReconstructLatestTime
    -- Turn on the finite rate particle chemistry. 
        Modifying /CASE/constant/cloudProperties:
        reactionModel    finiteRateParticleChemistry;
    -- Delete the folder "/CASE/[latest_timestep]/lagrangian/popePaticlesSet_1/"
    -- Decompose the latest time step. 
        calling ./DecomposeLatestTime
    -- Resume the simulation.
        calling ./ResumeParallelRun

Step-3. Continue with Step-2 for 10~50 time steps, and start the injection of 
    -- Pause the simulation. 
        Modifying /CASE/system/controlDict:
        stopAt    endTime;
    -- Change the start of injection for fuel particle to the latest time. 
        Modifying /CASE/constant/fuelCloudProperties:
        SOI    [latest_timestep];
    -- Resume the simulation. 
        calling ./ResumeParallelRun



To run the CRIEPI coal flame with inert fuel particles (kinematic): 
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
Following changes have to ba made to mmcMultiphaseFoam solver. 
In the directory: 
../mmcFoam-4.x/applications/solvers/mmc/mmcMultiphaseFoam

Modify: 
    createFuelCloud.H:: comment out line no. 1-16, and uncomment line no. 18-26. 

Delete/Comment out: 
    rhoEqn.H:39://      + fuelCloud.SM(rho)
    XiEqn.H:58://              + fuelCloud.SM(Xii)
    UEqn.H:11://      + fuelCloud.SuMass(U)
    mmcMultiphaseFoam.C:123://        #include "checkParticles.H" 

Recompile the source code and solver: 
    calling ./multiMake from ../mmcFoam-4.x/


